.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jan 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-init - Provisions a fresh server to become a Citadel Node


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel init [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Provisions a fresh server to become a Citadel Node. This command connects
the node to the AceTeam Network.

.PP
By default, citadel init only joins the network (no sudo required). Services
can be configured via the AceTeam web management page.

.PP
Use --provision for full provisioning including Docker installation, NVIDIA toolkit,
and system user configuration (requires sudo).


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--authkey\fP=""
	The pre-authenticated key to join the network

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for init

.PP
\fB--new-device\fP[=false]
	Force fresh registration, ignoring existing machine mapping

.PP
\fB--node-name\fP=""
	Set the node name (defaults to hostname)

.PP
\fB--provision\fP[=false]
	Full provisioning with Docker, NVIDIA toolkit, and services (requires sudo)

.PP
\fB--relogin\fP[=false]
	Force re-authentication while preserving IP address

.PP
\fB--service\fP=""
	Service to configure (vllm, ollama, llamacpp, none)

.PP
\fB--test\fP[=true]
	Run a diagnostic test after provisioning

.PP
\fB--verbose\fP[=false]
	Show detailed output during provisioning


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--auth-service\fP="https://aceteam.ai"
	The URL of the authentication service

.PP
\fB--config\fP=""
	config file (default is $HOME/.citadel-cli.yaml)

.PP
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--nexus\fP="https://nexus.aceteam.ai"
	The URL of the AceTeam Nexus server


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  # Default: join network only (no sudo required)
  citadel init

  # Full provisioning with Docker and NVIDIA toolkit (requires sudo)
  sudo citadel init --provision

  # Full provisioning with specific service
  sudo citadel init --provision --service vllm

  # Setup with pre-generated authkey (for CI/CD)
  citadel init --authkey <your-key>

  # Full provisioning with verbose output (for debugging)
  sudo citadel init --provision --verbose
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcitadel(1)\fP
